==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perpetrate
<hw>Per"pe*trate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Perpetrated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Perpetrating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>perpetratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>perpetrare</ets> to effect,
perpetrare; <ets>per</ets> + <ets>patrare</ets> to perform.]</ety>
<def>To do or perform; to carry through; to execute, commonly in a bad
sense; to commit (as a crime, an offense); to be guilty of; <as>as, to
<ex>perpetrate</ex> a foul deed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What the worst <qex>perpetrate</qex>, or best endure.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perpetration</ent>⟦br⟧
